timeline.content:
Dear UCL Accommodation Team,

I have already written a few emails expressing my need for second year UCL accommodation to no avail, so I am writing this to stress my situation and ask that you please consider me.

Knowing that second-year accommodation was not guaranteed, I have searched all relevant private student accommodation options, and at this point there is genuinely no room available for me that is within my price range. 

Though I was born in the UK, I grew up in Germany and still live there, meaning if I am unable to secure accommodation for my second year at UCL, there is no option for me to commute from home - I would literally have nowhere to live. Furthermore, I don‚Äôt have a UK based guarantor, so navigating the private housing sector is especially challenging as an international student who is paying her bills herself (as the money for an entire year is asked upfront).

I know this may not seem relevant (or may seem too personal), but the truth is that my parents would find it much more convenient for me to come back home and study in Germany, and my struggle to secure accommodation in London has made them start to pressure me more to do so - though I am adamant to remain at UCL.
